President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the State of Alaska in response to flooding that occurred from May 17 to June 11, 2013. This declaration allows federal funding to be provided to affected individuals and communities in order to assist with recovery efforts. Funding can be used for temporary housing, home repairs, and other programs to help individuals and business owners recover from the disaster. Additionally, federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Dolph A. Diemont has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance by registering online or calling the provided toll-free telephone numbers.